Package frc.alotobots.game

Class HMIStation

java.lang.Object
frc.alotobots.game.HMIStation
public class HMIStation extends Object
The DriverStation class represents the available inputs to the robot, providing access to controllers and defining buttons for various commands.

  • Method Details

    • driveFwdAxisRaw

      public double driveFwdAxisRaw()
      Gets the raw forward axis value for driving. The -1 multiplication inverts the joystick value because pushing forward returns a positive value, but we want forward motion to be negative in our coordinate system.
      Returns:
      The value used for driving forward with deadband applied.

    • driveFwdAxis

      public double driveFwdAxis()
      Gets the Drive Forward Axis with deadband, squared and rate limited
      Returns:
      double Forward Axis with deadband, squared and rate limited

    • driveStrAxisRaw

      public double driveStrAxisRaw()
      Gets the strafe raw axis value for driving. The -1 multiplication inverts the joystick value because pushing right returns a positive value, but we want right motion to be negative in our coordinate system.
      Returns:
      The strafe axis value with deadband applied.

    • driveStrAxis

      public double driveStrAxis()
      Gets the Drive Strafe Axis with deadband, squared and rate limited
      Returns:
      double Strafe Axis with deadband, squared and rate limited

    • driveRotAxisRaw

      public double driveRotAxisRaw()
      Gets the rotation axis value for driving. The -1 multiplication inverts the joystick value because pushing right returns a positive value, but we want clockwise rotation to be negative in our coordinate system.
      Returns:
      The rotation axis value with deadband applied.

    • driveRotAxis
